<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// encountered during extraction. It enables one to extract a sequence of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// values without error-checking and then checking for errors in bulk at the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// end. The class holds an Error object, so failing to check the result of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="50"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// the parse will result in a runtime error. The error flag is sticky and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="51"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// will cause all subsequent extraction functions to fail without even</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00052" /><CodeLine lineNumber="52"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// attempting to parse and without updating the Cursor offset. After clearing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00053" /><CodeLine lineNumber="53"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// the error flag, one can again use the Cursor object for parsing.</span></CodeLine>
